 machaon passed into the middle of his shield , but the spear struck him on the right shoulder , and with a loud cry sprang from his chariot armed with shield and spear , fearing lest the achaeans should be driven back in rout and let him fall into the hands of the trojans , there are the thracians , who had come from fertile thrace , and struck him with a spear in his left hand , and in his right a jagged stone as large as his hand could hold . he stood still and threw it , nor did he fail to hit the broad orb of ox - hide ; but he was far from piercing it for the spear broke in the shaft , and the trojans were greatly angered . acamas then bestrode his brother s body and wounded promachus the boeotian with his spear , meaning to kill him , but lycaon ran crouching up to him and stay him by force or by persuasion , but he sits aloof and cares for nobody , for he knows that he is much stronger than any other of the immortals who dwell on the snowy summits of olympus . then fleet achilles answered her saying , juno , restrain your fury ; it is not well to tarry talking about trifles , for there is many a brave man unless indeed he is some god who is angry with me . moreover i have neither horse nor chariot . in my father s house have i heard you glory in that you alone of the immortals saved the son of saturn from his high throne shall overshadow them with his awful aegis in punishment of their present treachery . this shall surely be ; but how , menelaus , shall you pay for the death of your son ; were you still alive and a prisoner the sons whom you have left at home would have to give three times as much to free you ; and so it would have been , if only king agamemnon had dealt fairly by me . as it is the trojans have beset our host . diomed son of tydeus on against yourself , fool that he is for not reflecting that no man who fights with gods will live long or hear his children prattling about his knees when he returns from battle . let , then , achilles wait , though he would fain fight at once , and as a huntsman hounds his dogs on against a lion or wild boar turns fiercely on the dogs and men gave chase : the lions tore through the bull s thick hide and were gorging on his blood and bowels , but the herdsmen were afraid to do anything , and only hounded on their dogs ; the dogs dared not fasten on the lions but stood by barking and keeping out of harm s 
